content.text:
Now I understand the structure. Countries are linked to leagues and matches, but not directly to players' nationalities. The "country" in this database refers to the country where the league/match takes place. Let me check if players with vision > 89 can be linked to countries through matches.

The claim says players with vision ≥ 90 are "from" certain countries. The database doesn't have player nationality — only which league/country's matches they played in. Let me interpret "from" as the countries (leagues) where these players appear in matches, and check.

input.command:
sqlite3 "/Users/david/workspace/claimdb/test_dbs/european_football_2.sqlite" "
SELECT DISTINCT c.name
FROM Player_Attributes pa
JOIN Player p ON pa.player_api_id = p.player_api_id
JOIN (
    SELECT DISTINCT home_player_1 as player_api_id, country_id FROM Match
    UNION SELECT DISTINCT home_player_2, country_id FROM Match
    UNION SELECT DISTINCT home_player_3, country_id FROM Match
    UNION SELECT DISTINCT home_player_4, country_id FROM Match
    UNION SELECT DISTINCT home_player_5, country_id FROM Match
    UNION SELECT DISTINCT home_player_6, country_id FROM Match
    UNION SELECT DISTINCT home_player_7, country_id FROM Match
    UNION SELECT DISTINCT home_player_8, country_id FROM Match
    UNION SELECT DISTINCT home_player_9, country_id FROM Match
    UNION SELECT DISTINCT home_player_10, country_id FROM Match
    UNION SELECT DISTINCT home_player_11, country_id FROM Match
    UNION SELECT DISTINCT away_player_1, country_id FROM Match
    UNION SELECT DISTINCT away_player_2, country_id FROM Match
    UNION SELECT DISTINCT away_player_3, country_id FROM Match
    UNION SELECT DISTINCT away_player_4, country_id FROM Match
    UNION SELECT DISTINCT away_player_5, country_id FROM Match
    UNION SELECT DISTINCT away_player_6, country_id FROM Match
    UNION SELECT DISTINCT away_player_7, country_id FROM Match
    UNION SELECT DISTINCT away_player_8, country_id FROM Match
    UNION SELECT DISTINCT away_player_9, country_id FROM Match
    UNION SELECT DISTINCT away_player_10, country_id FROM Match
    UNION SELECT DISTINCT away_player_11, country_id FROM Match
) mp ON mp.player_api_id = p.player_api_id
JOIN Country c ON c.id = mp.country_id
WHERE pa.vision > 89
ORDER BY c.name;
" 2>&1
input.description: Find countries where players with vision > 89 played

content.text:
The query results show that the distinct countries where players with vision scores > 89 appeared in matches are exactly: **England, France, Germany, Italy, and Spain**.

This matches the claim exactly. The five countries listed in the claim are the same five countries found in the database for players with vision > 89.

Let me also verify there are no other countries being missed (e.g., Belgium, Netherlands, etc. are NOT in the results):

input.command:
sqlite3 "/Users/david/workspace/claimdb/test_dbs/european_football_2.sqlite" "
SELECT c.name, COUNT(DISTINCT p.player_api_id) as player_count
FROM Player_Attributes pa
JOIN Player p ON pa.player_api_id = p.player_api_id
JOIN (
    SELECT home_player_1 as player_api_id, country_id FROM Match
    UNION SELECT home_player_2, country_id FROM Match
    UNION SELECT home_player_3, country_id FROM Match
    UNION SELECT home_player_4, country_id FROM Match
    UNION SELECT home_player_5, country_id FROM Match
    UNION SELECT home_player_6, country_id FROM Match
    UNION SELECT home_player_7, country_id FROM Match
    UNION SELECT home_player_8, country_id FROM Match
    UNION SELECT home_player_9, country_id FROM Match
    UNION SELECT home_player_10, country_id FROM Match
    UNION SELECT home_player_11, country_id FROM Match
    UNION SELECT away_player_1, country_id FROM Match
    UNION SELECT away_player_2, country_id FROM Match
    UNION SELECT away_player_3, country_id FROM Match
    UNION SELECT away_player_4, country_id FROM Match
    UNION SELECT away_player_5, country_id FROM Match
    UNION SELECT away_player_6, country_id FROM Match
    UNION SELECT away_player_7, country_id FROM Match
    UNION SELECT away_player_8, country_id FROM Match
    UNION SELECT away_player_9, country_id FROM Match
    UNION SELECT away_player_10, country_id FROM Match
    UNION SELECT away_player_11, country_id FROM Match
) mp ON mp.player_api_id = p.player_api_id
JOIN Country c ON c.id = mp.country_id
WHERE pa.vision > 89
GROUP BY c.name
ORDER BY c.name;
" 2>&1
